claim.claim-text:
21. A method for securing a mooring line of a vessel to a hooking means, comprising the steps of:
providing a hook having a pair of hook members defining a gap therebetween;
securing a heaving line to an eye of a mooring line of a vessel;
guiding said heaving line along a path which passes through said gap heaved, whereby when said heaving line heaves the eye past the hook, the eye locates over the hooking means; and
guiding said heaving line along a path such that the eye of the mooring line rides up the hook towards tips of the hook members as the heaving line heaves the eye past the hook.
